body:
This release includes support for the CAS 3.0 samlValidate endpoint (thanks @hamnis!).

It is backwards-compatible to Keycloak 4.6.0, in case you need the new feature but cannot upgrade immediately.
Release compatible with Keycloak 4.1.0.Final (no changes to previous release)
First release with new versioning scheme. From now on, the plugin version will match the Keycloak version it has been compiled and tested against.

This release adapts the plugin to the API changes in Keycloak 3.4.0.Final.

It has been tested to be compatible with Keycloak 3.2, 3.3 and 3.4.

Version 2.0.0 adapts the plugin to the SPI changes in Keycloak 3.2. The changes are backwards-incompatible, so **V2 no longer works with Keycloak <3.2**.

This is a beta release, use with caution!

The Keycloak CAS protocol plugin 1.0.0 adds support for CAS 1.0/2.0/3.0 compliant login/logout and service ticket validation, as well as single logout to Keycloak.

It has been tested against and is compatible with Keycloak 2.5.x, 3.0.x and 3.1.x.  
It is known to be incompatible with Keycloak 3.2.x.
